Late in the evening at the FSA campsite, your team is using just ine electic socket to supply all appliances with power. This socket has a single phase with 230V AC (RMS) and a 16A fuse. The lights in your tem tent use 100W. Cooking dinner for the hungry team on an electric stove uses 2500W. Six laptops, to prepare static events tomorrow, are plugged into the chargers at 65W each.A very hungry team member wants to make some popcorn in the microwave using 800W. How many laptops does he have to unplug to not blow the fuse which will not trip when plugging in / starting an appliance but will trip exactly at the specified power rating in the time it takes the popcorn to cook)

answer_options.answer_text: the fuse will blow even if all laptops are unplugged.

answer_options.answer_text: The team leader must write an apology email and upload the new document within 24 hours on order to avoid penalties.
The team has to upload a corrected version within 168 hours in order not to be de-registered from the event.
The team will receive 10 penalty points, which will be added to the total score.
